üîÑ Change Management & Issue Log SOP
A reference guide for tracking, reviewing, and approving all mapping, transformation, and data quality changes in the healthcare claims pipeline. Designed for auditability, accountability, and continuous improvement.

1. Purpose
Ensure all changes and known issues are logged, tracked, and resolved in a transparent, compliant manner.
Facilitate peer review, sign-off, and audit readiness for all critical data pipeline changes.
2. When to Log a Change or Issue
Field mapping or transformation logic is added, updated, or deprecated
Data quality gap (e.g., missing data, unexpected nulls, failed validation gate)
Business rules or requirements change
Production issue or bug is discovered
Field or table is added/removed/renamed
